definition.value: A layer which is determined by a form of vegetation.

value.value: Land is a planetary surface that is not covered by liquid.

Outer space is a hard vacuum containing a low density of particles, predominantly a plasma of hydrogen and helium as well as electromagnetic radiation, magnetic fields, neutrinos, dust and cosmic rays that exists between celestial bodies.
A material entity which is composed of one or more chemical entities and has neither independent shape nor volume but tends to expand indefinitely.
An object which is naturally occuring, bound together by gravitational or electromagnetic forces, and surrounded by space.

A planet is an astronomical body orbiting a star or stellar remnant that is massive enough to be rounded by its own gravity, is not massive enough to cause thermonuclear fusion, and has cleared its neighbouring region of planetesimals.
An object which is composed of one or more gravitationally bound structures that are associated with a position in space.

definition.value: A material part of an astronomical body.
An environmental material which is in a solid state.
An environmental material which is in a liquid state.

value.value: An astronomical body part which is composed of the combined mass of water found on, under, and over the surface of a planet.
A process whereby a volume of liquid moves due to a disequilibrium of physical forces.

definition.value: A process during which a volume of water is transported due to a disequilibria in physical forces.

label.value: environmental system determined by a quality

definition.value: An environmental system which is determined by materials bearing roughly homogeneous qualities.

label.value: environmental system determined by a material

definition.value: An environmental system within which an environmental material strongly influences the system's composition and properties.

value.value: An environmental system which includes both living and non-living components.

definition.value: An ice is an environmental material which is either frozen or which is maintained in a solid state by gravitational forces or pressure.

value.value: A quality which inheres in a astronomical body or astronomical body part by virtue of the variation in its material composition, participation in geological processes, and the variation in is land- and hydroforms.

definition.value: The surface layer of a volume of water.
A canopy which is composed of the aboveground portion, or crowns, of a community of crop plants.

value.value: A vegetation layer which is formed by a collection of individual plant crowns, themselves constituting part of the aboveground portion of a plant community.

An ecosystem which 1) is determined by communities of annual crops, perennial woody crops, or by actively tilled land, 2) is primarily used for agricultural activity, and 3) contains no village or larger human settlement.

definition.value: A layer which is primarily composed of some liquid material.
A layer which is primarily composed of some solid material, allowing for non-solid parts such as interstitial pockets of gas or liquid.
A geographic feature which is primarily composed of a continuous volume of liquid water held in shape or sustained by an environmental process.
A liquid surface layer which is in contact with air.
A liquid surface layer which is in contact with air.

value.value: A material transport process during which a volume of material is displaced due to a disequilirium in physical forces and during which 1) the qualities that inhere in that volume and 2) the processes that are unfolding within it are largely unchanged.

definition.value: A process in which includes the components of an environmental system as participants.

value.value: A general and temporary condition of partial or complete inundation of normally dry land areas from the overflow of inland and/or tidal waters, and/or the unusual and rapid accumulation or runoff of surface waters from any source. A great flow along a watercourse or a flow causing inundation of lands not normally covered by water.

definition.value: An environmental process which has water - in any of its states - as a participant.
A process during which material is displaced from its original location and transported either to a new location or back to the original location.
A substance, usually composed primarily of carbohydrates, fats, water and/or proteins, that can be eaten or drunk by an animal or human being for nutrition or pleasure.

A food product type is a class of food products that is differentiated by its food composition, processing and/or consumption characteristics. This does not include brand name products but it may include generic food dish categories.
